TEXT(beginproblem());

############################################################
# PG Setup Code
############################################################
$p = randomPerson();
$r = list_random(18,20);
$c = random(85,185,5);
$sol = $c/(1 + $r/100);
Context("Currency");
$bill = Currency("$sol");
Context("Interval");
Context()->flags->set(ignoreEndpointTypes => 1);
$interval = Interval("[50,$sol]");
Context("LinearRelation")->variables->are(x => 'Real');
Context()->noreduce('(-x)-y', '(-x)+y');
$relation = Formula("x + ($r/100)x <= $c");

############################################################
# Body
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML
The bill at a restaurant came and [$p] offered to pay for the whole table. We are not sure what the bill was, but it was at least [`\$50\text{.}`] [$p] added a tip, and the total came to [`\$[$c]\text{.}`] We are sure that [$p->they] added _at least_ [`[$r]\%`] tip. What might the original bill total have been before tip?

END_PGML

############################################################
# Scaffold
############################################################
Scaffold::Begin(numbered => 1,is_open => "correct_or_first_incorrect",can_open => always,);

############################################################
# Section
############################################################
Section::Begin("");

BEGIN_PGML
Write an inequality to represent this situation, using [`x`] to represent the bill total before tip was added.

[_]{$relation}{16}

END_PGML

Section::End();

############################################################
# Section
############################################################
Section::Begin("");

BEGIN_PGML
Solve this inequality. What's the most the bill could have been before tip?

[_]{$bill}{16}

END_PGML

Section::End();

############################################################
# Section
############################################################
Section::Begin("");

BEGIN_PGML
Use interval notation to express what the bill could have been before tip was added.

[_]{$interval}{16}

END_PGML

Section::End();

